4 Justice moved my Maker on high;
5 the divine power made me,
6 the highest wisdom and the primal love.

10 These words of dark color
11 I saw written at the top of a gate;
12 wherefore I said: “Master, their meaning is hard for me”.

13 And he to me, as one who is wise:
14 “Here it is necessary to abandon all suspicion;
15 all cowardice must be dead here.

49 The world does not allow any fame of them to exist;
50 mercy and justice disdain them:
51 let us not speak of them, but look and pass on”.

52 And I, who looked again, saw a banner
53 that whirling ran so swiftly,
54 that it seemed to me unworthy of any pause;

70 And after I gave myself to looking further,
71 I saw people on the bank of a great river;
72 wherefore I said: “Master, now grant me

109 Charon the demon, with eyes of burning coal,
110 beckoning to them, gathers them all;
111 he beats with his oar whoever lingers.

121 “My son,” said the courteous master,
122 “all those who die in the wrath of God
123 gather here from every country;

127 No good soul ever crosses here;
128 and therefore, if Charon complains about you,
129 you can now well understand what his words mean”.

133 The tearful earth gave forth a wind,
134 which flashed a crimson light
